5 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5090.2 of Title 74, unless there
7 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma Department of Commerce
9 Board. The Board shall constitute an advisory oversight board and
10 shall consist of nine (9) voting members, as follows:
11 1. Two members to be appointed by the President Pro Tempore of
12 the Senate; provided, at least one appointed member shall be from a
13 municipality with a population of fifty thousand (50,000) people or
14 less according to the latest Federal Decennial Census;
15 2. Two members to be appointed by the Speaker of the House of
16 Representatives; provided, at least one appointed member shall be
17 from a municipality with a population of fifty thousand (50,000)
18 people or less according to the latest Federal Decennial Census;
19 3. Four members to be appointed by the Governor; provided, at
20 least one appointed member shall be:
21 a. an economic development practitioner from this state,
22 and
